@2511 = ~Explosive Combustion~
@2512 = ~Explosive Combustion (Evocation, Necromancy)
Level: 5
Sphere: necromancy, elemental (fire)
Range: visual range of the caster
Duration: instantaneous
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 9-meters radius
Saving Throw: special

This spell suddenly flares up all creatures within the area of effect. The combustion is short but very intense, which has the effect of pulverizing the lesser creatures. The more resistant creatures, will be burned according to the following table:

1 or 2 HD: Explosion
3 or 4 HD: Explosion, death if saving throw is successful
5 or 6 HD: Death, 8D6 damage points if saving throw is successful
7 or 8 HD: 8D6 damage points, 4D6 if saving throw is successful
9 HD and +: 4D6 damage points, negates is saving throw is successful.

The creatures that explode are turned into dust and leaves no dead body behind. They cause an explosion of 8 meters radius that inflicts 4D6 points of fire damage (saving throw to halve) to all creatures within the area.
The creatures who "die" are turned into ashes by a smaller explosion, which extends over 5 meters and inflicts 2D6 points of fire damage (saving throw to halve).
The creatures that escape the explosion suffer from fire damage points, as indicated in the above table.
Saving Throws to minimize the effects of this spell are made with a -2 bonus, additional -1 every 5 levels of the caster beyond level 20. Saving Throws to split explosion damages are not reduced, the preacher does not affect them.
This spell has no effect over undead and cold and fire creatures.~

